---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Flame, Brain, Scale, Globe } from 'lucide-astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="Learn more about Overloaded and our mission to discuss burnout, mental health, and work-life balance.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-24 sm:py-32 dark:bg-linear-to-br dark:from-primary-950/20 dark:via-neutral-950 dark:to-neutral-950 light:bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight dark:text-neutral-100 light:text-neutral-900 mb-6">
          About <span class="text-primary-500">Overloaded</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl dark:text-neutral-400 light:text-neutral-600">
          Where it's okay to not have it all figured out
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl dark:bg-neutral-900/50 light:bg-white border dark:border-neutral-800 light:border-neutral-200 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold dark:text-neutral-100 light:text-neutral-900 mb-4">My Mission</h2>
            <p class="dark:text-neutral-300 light:text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
              We are drowning in advice. Everyone is a specialist nowadays, every guru has the solution or productivity 
              hack that will finally fix you. Did you notice that every "intellectual" nutritionist has a different "You should NOT consume this"? We live in a world with <span class="text-primary-500">endless information</span>, both sides of every issue are presented as absolute truths. So maybe you don't need more information. Maybe you need permission.
            </p>
            <p class="dark:text-neutral-300 light:text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              <span class="text-primary-500">Overloaded</span> isn't about adding to the noise, it's about creating space. Space to question. Space to be uncertain. You don't need an answer for everything. My mission is to actually make you reach the questions, and then, by your own critical thinking, find your own answers. 
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl dark:bg-neutral-900/50 light:bg-white border dark:border-neutral-800 light:border-neutral-200 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold dark:text-neutral-100 light:text-neutral-900 mb-4">What I Cover</h2>
            <ul class="space-y-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="shrink-0 mt-1">
                  <Flame size={24} strokeWidth={2} class="text-red-500" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="dark:text-neutral-100 light:text-neutral-900 font-semibold mb-1">Burnout Recognition & Recovery</h3>
                  <p class="dark:text-neutral-400 light:text-neutral-600">Discuss about modern society problems that leaves us feeling overwhelmed and exhausted.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="shrink-0 mt-1">
                  <Brain size={24} strokeWidth={2} class="text-purple-500" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="dark:text-neutral-100 light:text-neutral-900 font-semibold mb-1">Mental Health Awareness</h3>
                  <p class="dark:text-neutral-400 light:text-neutral-600">Breaking down stigma and exploring practical ways to maintain psychological well-being.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="shrink-0 mt-1">
                  <Scale size={24} strokeWidth={2} class="text-blue-500" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="dark:text-neutral-100 light:text-neutral-900 font-semibold mb-1">Work-Life Integration</h3>
                  <p class="dark:text-neutral-400 light:text-neutral-600">Finding sustainable ways to navigate modern work culture and personal life.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="shrink-0 mt-1">
                  <Globe size={24} strokeWidth={2} class="text-green-500" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="dark:text-neutral-100 light:text-neutral-900 font-semibold mb-1">Societal Challenges</h3>
                  <p class="dark:text-neutral-400 light:text-neutral-600">Question everything, challenge norms, and explore the complexities of the world we live in.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl dark:bg-neutral-900/50 light:bg-white border dark:border-neutral-800 light:border-neutral-200 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold dark:text-neutral-100 light:text-neutral-900 mb-4">Why This Matters</h2>
            <p class="dark:text-neutral-300 light:text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
              Society is at the peak of depression, anxiety, burnout, uncertainty, and confusion. The reason? There are many, actually. We will never find a single reason, but now it's too late to go back to "Ignorance is bliss," isn't it? So I want to use this blog and the people who follow it to try our best to live better, even while being fully aware of the chaos.
            </p>
            <p class="dark:text-neutral-300 light:text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
              The revolutionary act isn't finding all the answers. It's giving yourself permission to exist in the questions. 
              To be confused, uncertain, and still moving forward. This platform exists as a reminder: you're not broken for 
              feeling overwhelmed. You're human. And that's more than enough.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl dark:bg-linear-to-br dark:from-primary-950/30 dark:to-neutral-900/50 light:bg-primary-50 border dark:border-primary-800/50 light:border-primary-200 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold dark:text-neutral-100 light:text-neutral-900 mb-4">Join the Conversation</h2>
            <p class="dark:text-neutral-300 light:text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Whether you're experiencing burnout, supporting someone who is, 
              or simply interested in these important topics, you're welcome here.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
              <a 
                href="/blog" 
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border border-transparent text-base font-medium rounded-full text-white bg-primary-500 hover:bg-primary-600 transition-colors"
              >
                Read Our Articles
              </a>
              <a 
                href="/#subscribe" 
                aria-label="Subscribe to Overloaded newsletter for burnout and mental health insights"
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border dark:border-neutral-700 light:border-neutral-300 text-base font-medium rounded-full dark:text-neutral-100 light:text-neutral-900 dark:hover:border-neutral-600 light:hover:border-neutral-400 dark:hover:bg-neutral-900 light:hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors"
              >
                Subscribe to Newsletter
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
